data.name: Savory Cheese Waffles
data.quickTastyDescription: Crispy on the outside and cheesy on the inside, these savory waffles are a delightful twist on breakfast or a tasty snack!
detailedCookingInstructions: In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, and salt.
In another bowl, whisk together the eggs and milk until well combined.
Add the melted butter to the egg mixture and stir.
Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix until just combined.
Fold in the shredded cheddar cheese.
Preheat your waffle iron according to the manufacturer's instructions.
Pour the batter onto the preheated waffle iron, using enough to cover the surface without overflowing.
Cook according to your waffle iron's instructions, usually about 5 minutes, until golden brown and crispy.
Carefully remove the waffle and repeat with the remaining batter.
